Former Governor of Anambra State and a frontline presidential aspirant of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP), Peter Obi has called on Nigerians to get registered and get their Permanent Voters Card (PVC) ready to enable them to exercise their franchise in the forthcoming general election. Peter Obi who made the call on Wednesday via his official Twitter handle asked his teaming supporters to ensure their data is captured by the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) before the deadline. It could be recalled that the INEC Chairman had said the online registration for the PVC will end on May 30 while the physical registration will elapse in June. -Advertisement- Reacting to the development, Obi wrote, “Fellow Nigerians, to exercise your constitutional right to elect leaders of your choice, you must vote. To vote, you must be registered. “INEC PVC online and Physical Registration end on 30th May and 30th June, respectively. Don’t miss the deadlines”.